Ukraine Harvests 9.7 Million Tons of Grain, Ministry Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-07-14T13:50:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/ukraine-harvests-9-7-million-tons-of-grain-ministry-says-1-.html
Ukraine harvested 9.7 million metric
tons of grain from 3.4 million hectares (8.4 million acres) this
season as of today, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  Average yields increased to 2.85 tons a hectare from 2.43
tons a hectare a year earlier, the Kiev-based ministry said in
e-mailed statement today.  Farmers reaped 5.7 million tons of wheat from 1.8 million
hectares. Wheat yields increased to 3.1 tons a hectare from 2.7
tons last year, according to the ministry.  Average barley yields also gained to 2.6 tons a hectare
from 2.3 tons, the ministry said. Some 3.8 million tons of
barley have been gathered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  